column2: Councillor Jim Furfaro Review and Amend the City of Guelph Tree Bylaw
column5:
The existing City of Guelph Tree Bylaw needs to be reviewed and amended.

The current bylaw does not regulate lots under .5 acres (i.e. most of the residential lots in town).

The existing bylaw is far too lenient and allows residential owners to cut down mature,,,Review and Amend the City of Guelph Tree Bylaw The existing City of Guelph Tree Bylaw needs to be reviewed and amended.
